Class AeProcessViewBase

java.lang.Object
  org.activebpel.rt.bpeladmin.war.web.processview.AeProcessViewBase
Direct Known Subclasses:
AeProcessViewBean
public class AeProcessViewBase
extends java.lang.Object

Base class for used by the presentation beans responsible for displaying process details. TODO (pj/cck) javascrtipt for jsp duplicated for deployed and active process, plus doesn't account for pick as sole activity.

mMode

private int mMode
Indicates the which mode the process view is based on. The mode can be ACTIVE_PROCESS_DETAIL for an active process instance given the pid or DEPLOYED_PROCESS_DETAIL for a deployed process given the pdid (process detail id) or planId.

initialize

protected void initialize()
Initializes the bean by retrieving the BPEL and State documents for the selected process, followed by building a simple model representing the Process and its current state.

This method is called when the presenation layer (JSP) sets process id via setProcessIdStr() method.
